"{\"uid\": \"theatlantic.com-family-archive-2024-08-adult-gymnastics-olympics-679314\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Competitors in the sport are getting older, transforming the image of a gymnast from meek little girl to empowered athlete.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 123, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2016, the two-time Olympic gymnast Aly Raisman was known for her incredible floor routine \\u2026 and penchant for naps.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 163, \"end\": 174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aly_Raisman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aly Raisman\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aly_Raisman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aly_Raisman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Raisman, the oldest member of the team, took the chance to snooze whenever she could get it.\", \"from\": 243, \"to\": 335, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Simone Biles jokingly called her \\\"our sleeping little grandma.\\\"\", \"from\": 336, \"to\": 399, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Raisman was 22 years old.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So, you know, ancient.\", \"from\": 426, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"By 2021, at the Tokyo Olympics, Biles was 24 and had earned the \\\"grandma\\\" nickname herself.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, Biles is 27, she's competing at her third Olympics, and the average age of an athlete on the U.S. women's gymnastics team is about22 and a half.\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 697, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Bilesrecently apologized to Raisman, saying that she's learned what it's like to be a \\\"grandma.\\\"\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 794, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Her body hurts more.\", \"from\": 795, \"to\": 815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She needs more rest after competitions.\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 855, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I have to say: I feel her pain.\", \"from\": 856, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I myself am a gymnast-and I am turning 40 this year.\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 945, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unfortunately,I did not make the 2024 Olympic Team.\", \"from\": 946, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am watching all those grandma gymnasts from home, with my adult gymnastics squad.\", \"from\": 998, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The youngest among us are in their 20s; the oldest is in her 50s.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"About half of the team had never done gymnastics before joining this class.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1223, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We train together two days a week and compete a few times a year.\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At our gym, when the little girls learn new skills, they get a beaded jewel.\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1366, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When we do, we win an Advil.\", \"from\": 1367, \"to\": 1395, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We need more naps than Raisman or Biles, but you could not pay us to stay home from class.\", \"from\": 1396, \"to\": 1486, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the past decade, interest in adult gymnastics has exploded, coinciding with the growing age of champions around the world.\", \"from\": 1488, \"to\": 1613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For years, successful female gymnaststraditionally peakedat 15 or 16 years old.\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many trained under abusive conditions.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1732, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They competed for their coaches or their countries, not themselves.\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1800, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But now gymnastics isdominatedby women in their mid- to late 20s (and even early 30s) who want to win on their own terms.\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1922, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Their longevity is inspiring more grown-ups, both amateur and professional, to return to the sport-and encouraging others, who might never have thought gymnastics would welcome them, to learn to flip too.\", \"from\": 1923, \"to\": 2127, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Unlike me, Stacey Tirro did not do gymnastics as a child.\", \"from\": 2129, \"to\": 2186, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2140, \"end\": 2146, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stacey_Slater\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1579425734938102e-28, \"text\": \"Stacey\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stacey_Slater\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stacey_Slater\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But when she saw the joy on her kids' faces as they bounced on a trampoline in their gymnastics classes, she decided she also wanted to experience that.\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2339, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"So what if she was 36, practically dead in gymnastics years?\", \"from\": 2340, \"to\": 2400, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2008, she worked up the courage to join that gym's adult class.\", \"from\": 2401, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She's been tracking her progress under the name \\\"The Geriatric Gymnast\\\" ever since.\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2551, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tirro was lucky there was a class to join at all.\", \"from\": 2553, \"to\": 2602, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the early 2010s, grown-up gymnasts were pretty much on their own.\", \"from\": 2603, \"to\": 2671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Insurance for adult classes is expensive, so the most common options were \\\"open gym sessions\\\"-essentially, loosely supervised free-for-alls where you could bounce on the trampoline and launch yourself into the foam pit, but where you would not necessarily learn much.\", \"from\": 2672, \"to\": 2939, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gina Paulhus, who was in her 20s at the time, did take classes but told me she had to train with high-school girls.\", \"from\": 2940, \"to\": 3055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2940, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Holby_City\", \"score\": 0.9324602302599436, \"rank\": 0.07243179660471392, \"text\": \"Gina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Holby_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Holby_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Eager to find gymnasts her own age, she started a Facebook group called \\\"Just like fine wine \\u2026 Adult Gymnastics Group\\\" in 2014.\", \"from\": 3056, \"to\": 3183, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3157, \"end\": 3167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9999993647126957, \"rank\": 6.352880039295107e-07, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She later founded anAdult Gymnastics Camp.\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3210, \"end\": 3220, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9999993647126957, \"rank\": 6.352880039295107e-07, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Tirro and Paulhus were outliers.\", \"from\": 3227, \"to\": 3263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In general, serious gymnastics-the kind where you go and learn skills and try to get better-was still just for kids.\", \"from\": 3264, \"to\": 3380, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That's largely because, starting in the 1970s, coaches in America perceived \\\"little girls in pretty boxes\\\" as more trainable than adults.\", \"from\": 3382, \"to\": 3519, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Well into the 2010s, a brutal coaching culture remained: Keep 'em weak, keep 'em hungry, keep 'em doubtful and dependent.\", \"from\": 3520, \"to\": 3641, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That, the conventional wisdom went, was the only way to win.\", \"from\": 3642, \"to\": 3702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Girls did what they were told-and when they were too physically or mentally broken, they were disposed of.\", \"from\": 3703, \"to\": 3809, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The long line of little girls desperate to go to the Olympics never ended, after all.\", \"from\": 3810, \"to\": 3895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This culture was set in part by the most notorious coaches of the modern era: B\\u00e9la and M\\u00e1rta K\\u00e1rolyi.\", \"from\": 3897, \"to\": 3998, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3984, \"end\": 3997, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rta_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"score\": 0.9999999991350705, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"M\\u00e1rta K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rta_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/M\\u00e1rta_K\\u00e1rolyi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From the 1970s to the late '90s, B\\u00e9la coached and took credit for the successes of the Olympians Nadia Com\\u0103neci, Mary Lou Retton, Kim Zmeskal, Betty Okino-and a dozen more gymnasts you may have heard of but hundreds more you likely have not.\", \"from\": 3999, \"to\": 4240, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4096, \"end\": 4110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"score\": 0.9999999839874364, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Nadia Com\\u0103neci\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nadia_Com\\u0103neci\"}, {\"begin\": 4112, \"end\": 4127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Lou_Retton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mary Lou Retton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Lou_Retton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mary_Lou_Retton\"}, {\"begin\": 4129, \"end\": 4140, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Zmeskal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kim Zmeskal\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Zmeskal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Zmeskal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"His methods were ruthless.\", \"from\": 4241, \"to\": 4267, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1991, anotherhigh-level coach saidthat K\\u00e1rolyi gymnasts \\\"do not so much retire as expire.\\\"\", \"from\": 4268, \"to\": 4361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4310, \"end\": 4317, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"score\": 0.6938734032991568, \"rank\": 0.42712626451854313, \"text\": \"K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"B\\u00e9la's wife, M\\u00e1rta, was in charge of the U.S. women's national team from 2001 to 2016, training them at the \\\"K\\u00e1rolyi Ranch.\\\"\", \"from\": 4362, \"to\": 4486, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4471, \"end\": 4478, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"score\": 0.7007088441465716, \"rank\": 0.42712626451854313, \"text\": \"K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According toan independent investigationcommissioned by the U.S. Olympic & Paralympic Committee, no parents were allowed there during training camps.\", \"from\": 4487, \"to\": 4636, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Biles has said that she and other underfed gymnastsbroke into the cafeteria at nightto steal food.\", \"from\": 4637, \"to\": 4735, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Ranch was also whereseveral gymnasts saythe former national-team doctor Larry Nassar sexually abused them under the guise of medical care.\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4736, \"end\": 4745, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Ranch\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.350644833819642e-23, \"text\": \"The Ranch\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Ranch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Ranch\"}, {\"begin\": 4812, \"end\": 4824, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"score\": 0.9986437956255909, \"rank\": 0.0013580461622554245, \"text\": \"Larry Nassar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"(M\\u00e1rta later saidthat she felt \\\"extremely bad\\\" about Nassar's abuse but that she did not \\\"feel responsible.\\\"\", \"from\": 4879, \"to\": 4987, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4932, \"end\": 4938, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2370811093971042e-79, \"text\": \"Nassar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The K\\u00e1rolyisalso denied claimsthat they themselves were abusive.)\", \"from\": 4988, \"to\": 5053, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This culture trickled down, and coaches around the country modeled their practices after the K\\u00e1rolyis.\", \"from\": 5055, \"to\": 5157, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Many believed the lie that broken bones and broken spirits weresigns of hard work.\", \"from\": 5158, \"to\": 5240, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a kid, my teammates and I never rose to the level of Biles or Raisman.\", \"from\": 5241, \"to\": 5314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But our coaches still gave us cruel nicknames related to our weight, pitted us against one another, and pushed us to train on injured limbs.\", \"from\": 5315, \"to\": 5455, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We were too afraid to mention our pain.\", \"from\": 5456, \"to\": 5495, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We were kids.\", \"from\": 5496, \"to\": 5509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We did not know better.\", \"from\": 5510, \"to\": 5533, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's horrible to have that in common with the most successful gymnasts in the world.\", \"from\": 5535, \"to\": 5619, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Read: Simone Biles and the limits of 'work ethic'  Then, in 2016,Rachael Denhollander, a former gymnast, and an anonymous gymnastics Olympic medalistfiled complaintsagainst Nassar.\", \"from\": 5621, \"to\": 5801, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5686, \"end\": 5706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Denhollander\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Rachael Denhollander\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Denhollander\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rachael_Denhollander\"}, {\"begin\": 5794, \"end\": 5800, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2370811093971042e-79, \"text\": \"Nassar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By 2018,more than 265 victimshad been identified, and high-profile stars, including Raisman and Biles, had joined the chorus.\", \"from\": 5802, \"to\": 5927, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The national teamstopped trainingat the K\\u00e1rolyi Ranch, and Nassar was sentenced to a total of 140 to 360 years in prison for all of the charges against him.\", \"from\": 5928, \"to\": 6084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5968, \"end\": 5975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"score\": 0.7007088441465716, \"rank\": 0.42712626451854313, \"text\": \"K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mih\\u00e1ly_K\\u00e1rolyi\"}, {\"begin\": 5987, \"end\": 5993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2370811093971042e-79, \"text\": \"Nassar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, the independent investigation commissioned by the U.S. Olympic & Paralympic Committee estimated that Nassar had abusedmore than 400children and young adults.\", \"from\": 6085, \"to\": 6254, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6198, \"end\": 6204, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2370811093971042e-79, \"text\": \"Nassar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q2159907\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Larry_Nassar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gymnastics' brutal culture of perfectionism has not totally disappeared.\", \"from\": 6256, \"to\": 6328, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But in the past several years, grown women have started to transform the image of a gymnast from meek little girl to empowered athlete.\", \"from\": 6329, \"to\": 6464, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They have proved that they can win medals on their own terms, and many modern coaches have come to recognize that success does not require breaking young girls.\", \"from\": 6465, \"to\": 6625, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If the culture is set by the most successful, then Biles and her coaches, C\\u00e9cile Canqueteau-Landi and Laurent Landi, are the new models.\", \"from\": 6626, \"to\": 6762, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6728, \"end\": 6741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Landi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Laurent Landi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Landi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Laurent_Landi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When Biles pulled out of the Tokyo Olympics in 2021to protect her mental and physical health, the Landis supported her decision.\", \"from\": 6763, \"to\": 6891, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When she decided to make another run in 2024, the Landis followedher lead.\", \"from\": 6892, \"to\": 6966, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Katie Walsh, the director of the Netflix documentarySimone Rising,calls the relationship between Biles and her coaches \\\"collaborative.\", \"from\": 6967, \"to\": 7101, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6967, \"end\": 6978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Walsh_(jockey)\", \"score\": 0.7867161401851925, \"rank\": 0.27110582639697917, \"text\": \"Katie Walsh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Walsh_(jockey)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Walsh_(jockey)\"}, {\"begin\": 7000, \"end\": 7007, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.955902463794514e-20, \"text\": \"Netflix\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netflix\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Both coach and gymnast have agency.\", \"from\": 7101, \"to\": 7137, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Prioritizing athletes' well-being has made it easier for gymnasts to excel as they get older.\", \"from\": 7139, \"to\": 7232, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2022,new managementat USAG (the governing body of the sport in the United States) pledged to build up athletes \\\"mentally and emotionally.\\\"\", \"from\": 7233, \"to\": 7374, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7258, \"end\": 7262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"USAG\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Gymnastics\"}, {\"begin\": 7303, \"end\": 7316, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999883928922522, \"rank\": 1.1607128602336289e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Add in advances in sports medicine and smart training practices, and more older gymnasts are physically able to keep competing.\", \"from\": 7375, \"to\": 7502, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Injuries are still inevitable, but they might not be career-ending anymore.\", \"from\": 7503, \"to\": 7578, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can take the time you need to heal without aging out of the sport before the next Olympic cycle.\", \"from\": 7579, \"to\": 7679, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Those injured at or just before the Olympic trials this year-Skye Blakely, age 19; Kayla DiCello, 20; and Shilese Jones, 22- might make another run in 2028 in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 7680, \"to\": 7851, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7763, \"end\": 7776, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayla_DiCello\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kayla DiCello\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayla_DiCello\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kayla_DiCello\"}, {\"begin\": 7786, \"end\": 7799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shilese Jones\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shilese_Jones\"}, {\"begin\": 7839, \"end\": 7850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.2714111185229053e-18, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Even the 2012 all-around gold medalist, Gabby Douglas, wants to compete in L.A., at which point she will be 32.\", \"from\": 7852, \"to\": 7963, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7892, \"end\": 7905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabby Douglas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Douglas\"}, {\"begin\": 7927, \"end\": 7931, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3985070358135937e-15, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The change in culture haspushed more gyms to welcome whole teams of non-elite adult gymnasts searching for community and the kind of joy they can find only upside-down.\", \"from\": 7965, \"to\": 8133, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When the old culture imploded, grown-ups like me returned, determined to redefine our relationship with a sport that we love but that almost destroyed us.\", \"from\": 8134, \"to\": 8288, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's awesome to have that in common with the most successful gymnasts in the world.\", \"from\": 8290, \"to\": 8373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After all, the sport itself was never the problem.\", \"from\": 8375, \"to\": 8425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It certainly comes with risks-annual injuries in gymnastics among childrenrival those in some contact sports.\", \"from\": 8426, \"to\": 8535, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But it also has benefits.\", \"from\": 8536, \"to\": 8561, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Research has found thatit may actually be good for a person, at any age, to invert their body.\", \"from\": 8562, \"to\": 8656, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One gymnast I spoke with, Serina Gelinas, told me that it helps her with sensory-processing issues.A recent study in Indonesiashowed that basic gymnastics can lower blood pressure and cholesterol in women older than 65.\", \"from\": 8657, \"to\": 8876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8683, \"end\": 8689, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serina,_Lombardy\", \"score\": 0.7732558117839546, \"rank\": 0.15789473684213493, \"text\": \"Serina\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serina,_Lombardy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serina,_Lombardy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And the mental fortitude and perseverance needed to convince yourself to even get up on a 10-centimeter-wide beam-let alone flip on one-make \\\"adult\\\" tasks such as public speaking and negotiating a raise seem like pieces of cake.\", \"from\": 8877, \"to\": 9105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Tirro, the Geriatric Gymnast, trains with and now also coaches an adult class atFlipper's Gymnasticsin New Jersey.\", \"from\": 9107, \"to\": 9221, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She told me the culture change has even affected women, like her, who did not grow up doing gymnastics.\", \"from\": 9222, \"to\": 9325, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Elite \\\"grandma\\\" gymnasts inspire Tirro because their success is evidence that \\\"old\\\" people are capable of more than they might think.\", \"from\": 9326, \"to\": 9459, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Watching them find joy in what they do, potential gymnasts of all ages might decide to try the sport for themselves.\", \"from\": 9460, \"to\": 9576, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Gina Paulhus's Facebook group now has more than 13,000 members.\", \"from\": 9578, \"to\": 9641, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9578, \"end\": 9582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Holby_City\", \"score\": 0.9324602302599436, \"rank\": 0.07243179660471392, \"text\": \"Gina\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Holby_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Characters_of_Holby_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She keeps a spreadsheet of gyms that host adult classes or open gym sessions-at least 445 in the United States alone.\", \"from\": 9642, \"to\": 9759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9739, \"end\": 9752, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999883928922522, \"rank\": 1.1607128602336289e-05, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year, the U.S. hosted its firstMasters Gymnastics World Cup, in which about 200 gymnasts, men and women, ages 30 and up, competed-some traveling from as far away as Germany and Japan.\", \"from\": 9760, \"to\": 9948, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 9930, \"end\": 9937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"score\": 0.56086211806106, \"rank\": 0.7829656350379013, \"text\": \"Germany\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nazi_Germany\"}, {\"begin\": 9942, \"end\": 9947, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"score\": 0.9999998969888164, \"rank\": 1.0255110883859928e-07, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Reddit spacer/gymnasticshas even banned posts starting with \\\"Am I too old \\u2026 ?\\\"\", \"from\": 9949, \"to\": 10031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer, moderators say, is boring because it's always the same: \\\"No, you are not too old to start.\\\"\", \"from\": 10032, \"to\": 10135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TheAtlantic.com \\u00a92026The Atlantic Monthly Group.\", \"from\": 10137, \"to\": 10185, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10162, \"end\": 10178, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Atlantic Monthly\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Atlantic\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 10186, \"to\": 10206, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This site is protected by reCAPTCHA and the GooglePrivacy PolicyandTerms of Serviceapply\", \"from\": 10208, \"to\": 10296, \"entities\": []}]}"